## Task 1: CSS Basics

**CSS** (Cascading Style Sheets) is a language used to style HTML elements. It controls the appearance of web pages, including colors, fonts, layout, and more. CSS separates the content (HTML) from the presentation (CSS), making websites more maintainable and easier to update.

**Example:**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>CSS Basics</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: lightblue;
            color: white;
            font-size: 24px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to CSS!</h1>
    <p>This is a paragraph styled with CSS.</p>
</body>
</html>
```

**Explanation:**

- **`body` selector:** Targets the entire body of the HTML document.
- **`background-color` property:** Sets the background color to light blue.
- **`color` property:** Sets the text color to white.
- **`font-size` property:** Sets the font size to 24 pixels.

This simple example demonstrates how CSS can be used to change the overall appearance of a web page. By applying styles to different HTML elements, you can create visually appealing and customized websites.
